= Martial Law

Papen has continued to assert his independence against Schleicher's advice and is still planning to declare martial law, dissolve the Reichstag, and cancel elections indefinitely when the Reichstag convenes this week, as he announced to the cabinet. With an increasing amount of Labor protests on the streets, and uncompromising hostility from every corner of German society, Schleicher simply cannot support his former friend anymore, and his quest to commit political suicide with the approval of President Hindenburg.

Schleicher has also been distancing himself from Papen and his unpopular policies in preparation for his chancellorship, through conversations with our trade unions and a wide variety of political leaders like Gregor Strasser.

One thing is clear: Papen must go for German democracy to survive.

