His successor is Schleicher himself—having orchestrated Papen's fall through rigged war games, he has now been appointed chancellor with the full support of the president. His appointment is a breath of fresh air compared to Papen, and his more moderate and social leanings are more acceptable to the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>.

However, many still view Schleicher as little better than his predecessor. After all, he was responsible for the[? if otl_prussian_coup_seen:&nbsp;Prussian coup and the?] disastrous policies of the Papen government. At the end of the day, he's just another <span style="color: #808080;">reactionary</span>.